AI-based interview questions 


How would you test an AI system differently from a traditional application?

Traditional systems are deterministic:
* Same input → same output
AI systems are probabilistic:
* The same intent may generate slightly different outputs
So testing strategy changes.

A. Data Validation
* Input document quality
* Corrupted files
* OCR noise
* Language variance
* Adversarial inputs
B. Model Validation
* Accuracy
* Precision/Recall/F1
* CER/WER for OCR
* Hallucination rate
* Confidence scoring
C. Workflow Validation
* End-to-end business outcome validation
* Human review routing
* Retry/fallback behavior
* Escalation logic
D. Governance Validation
* Explainability
* Audit logs
* Traceability
* Bias checks
* PII masking validation
E. Production Monitoring
* Drift detection
* Model degradation
* Latency spikes
* Prompt regression
* Golden dataset comparison
Strong Closing Line
“In AI systems, correctness is not only about functional validation — it’s about reliability boundaries, confidence behavior, explainability, and operational trust.”


